**Title:** From Initial Formation to Developmental Refinement: GABAergic Inputs Shape Neuronal Subnetworks in the Primary Somatosensory Cortex  
**DOI:** [10.48324/dandi.001349/0.250520.1729](https://doi.org/10.48324/dandi.001349/0.250520.1729)  
**Description:**  
This Dandiset contains calcium imaging data acquired via two-photon microscopy in the primary somatosensory cortex of developing mice (postnatal days P11–P21). Simultaneously, behavioral video recordings were collected. Imaging and behavior were synchronized using an LED signal. Data analysis utilized both standard and custom Python/MATLAB code.  
**Species:** Mus musculus (House mouse)  
**Modalities:** Two-photon calcium imaging, synchronized behavioral video  
**Number of subjects:** 32  
**Number of files:** 361  
**Total size:** ~9 GB  
**Data Format:** Neurodata Without Borders (NWB)

Huang, Jui-Yen (2025) From Initial Formation to Developmental Refinement: GABAergic Inputs Shape Neuronal Subnetworks in the Primary Somatosensory Cortex (Version 0.250520.1729) [Data set]. DANDI Archive.  
[https://doi.org/10.48324/dandi.001349/0.250520.1729](https://doi.org/10.48324/dandi.001349/0.250520.1729)

- Imaging data: Processed and raw fluorescence, segmented cells, analytical outputs
- Behavioral synchronization (LED triggers)
- Experimental metadata (age, genotype, imaging parameters)

- Cell population imaging
- Analytical and surgical techniques
